    "updated_at": "2015-05-23T16:43:09Z",
    "body": "@zcbenz I can still reproduce this issue with 0.26.1. Its a bit hard to repro, but here are the steps:\n- run electron 0.26.1 after downloading it, no need to write our own app\n- open devtools\n- after the opening body element add `<textarea id=\"tt\"></textarea>\"`\n- use another editor to copy the following value into the clipboard: Jøhänñéß\n- paste into the text area\n- use the devtools and type `new Buffer(document.getElementById(\"tt\").value).toString()`\n\n=> the resulting string is: \"Jøhän\" and we lost some bytes. When you inspect the buffer you will see that its byte length is only 7. \n"
  },
